      passage: `The Seljuk Empire, which held sway over central Asia from roughly 1037 CE to 1194 CE, drew profit from trading with its neighbors: its merchants shipped out fruit, silk, and cotton and _____ other valuable goods&mdash;gold, silver, and agate among them&mdash;that were then traded locally.`,
